news.title: Kolkata development body plans weekly inspection of its plots
news.para: KMDA owns several plots in areas like Patuli, Baisnabghata, Kasba, Rajdanga and adjacent to the Ruby crossing, besides in the east Kolkata area.

news.title: Carry out structural audit & repairs of old buildings: Kolhapur civic body
news.para: The Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) issued a public disclosure on Friday in this regard. KMC city engineer Netradip Sarnobat said, “It has been observed that many buildings in Kolhapur city are in a dangerous condition."

news.title: No HC stay, Panvel civic body to continue with property tax collection
news.para: Meanwhile, a hearing on a public interest petition filed by Kharghar Forum against the property tax collection by the civic body in retrospective manner was held on March 26, in the high court.

news.title: Over 1,200 units allotted in three affordable housing projects in Bhubaneswar
news.para: In the first phase of allotment, Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA), which executed the housing projects for the urban poor at Chandrasekharpur, Satya Nagar and Subuddhipur, had handed over the keys of homes to 659 beneficiaries.

news.title: Edelweiss invests Rs 775 crore in Prateek Realtors and Suruchi Properties
news.para: "Edelweiss has done two investments in the real estate side from its special situation fund ₹11,000 crore in the last week and is closing on with the next investment in a manufacturing company," said a source.

news.title: UltraTech Cement faces demand order of Rs 21.13 crore from Chhattisgarh government
news.para: "The company has received a demand order from the Collector, Balodabazar, Mining Department, Chhattisgarh, for an amount of Rs 21.13 crore against minimum production requirement as per the Mine Development and Production Agreement ("MDPA")," said UltraTech.

news.title: Nearly half of 611 C&D sites in Delhi haven't installed air quality sensors
news.para: Delhi's 611 C&D sites lack sensors. Alerts for data absence and high PM10 levels. TERI and ARAI study shows dust pollution's significant contribution to Delhi's air pollution.

news.title: Property registration in Maharashtra to remain open over this weekend
news.para: ​The registrar offices across the state remained open on Friday despite it being a public holiday on account of Good Friday. The registrar offices will also work on Saturday, March 30, and Sunday, March 31, to facilitate this.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Residents protest at Arvind SmartSpaces' office
news.para: Flat owners claimed that Arvind SmartSpaces Ltd had promised allotted parking for each of the 576 flats but had provided space for only 100-150 cars.

news.title: Landlords in United Kingdom bet on green offices as hybrid work makes tenants picky
news.para: UK commercial property firms have cashed in on this trend, logging steady growth in rental incomes and occupancy rates over the last year even as elevated interest rates hamper growth elsewhere in their business.

news.title: Rexford Industrial Realty buys properties for $1 billion from Blackstone Real Estate
news.para: Rexford has acquired about 3 million square feet of industrial properties located in Southern California for about $332 per square foot on average.

news.title: China: Country Garden says expects to suspend stock listing
news.para: Country Garden is among several of China's largest developers to face setbacks in recent years, along with Evergrande and Vanke, fuelling concerns about the stability of the world's second-largest economy.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC property tax mop-up past Rs 1,000 crore, half of MCD
news.para: NDMC’s total collection from property tax stood at Rs 933 crore in FY 2022-23, Rs 951 crore in FY 2021-22 and Rs 690 crore in FY 2020-21.

news.title: China Vanke posts 50.6% drop in 2023 core profit
news.para: Investors have been dumping China Vanke's shares and bonds in the past few weeks, triggering a rare central government directive to help the Shenzhen-based developer beat a liquidity crisis.

news.title: BMC issues notice to Mumbai metro contractors over Rs 370 crore property tax default
news.para: The civic body said that as Metro works are ongoing at several locations in the city, the contractors are contractually liable to pay the property tax of the casting yard plot.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body postpones sale of 22 plots due to Lok Sabha election
news.para: ​Before the code was enacted, the AMC had already announced the public auction of these plots, with a cumulative base price of Rs 2,250 crore.

news.title: Jaipur development body, JMC demolishes five illegal colonies
news.para: Officials said around 150 places on both sides of the footpath and road were illegally occupied by squatters who put up carts, tarpaulins, hoardings, signboards, iron angles, platforms, tin shaded tables and chairs among others.

news.title: Kochi civic body to let 'total' construction in risk zones prone to flooding
news.para: Kochi corporation master plan, that has been approved by town planning department, envisages giving approval for total construction in the areas instead of the 50% approved earlier.

news.title: Madurai civic body nets 77% property tax in FY24
news.para: Madurai corporation has collected Rs 223 crore out of the targeted Rs 352 crore, including tax arrears, until March. This was 15% more than that collected in the previous fiscal when the corporation netted Rs 192 crore of which arrears accounted for Rs 35 crore.

news.title: China: Property developers' 2023 results hit by sector downturn
news.para: China's property sector, a pillar of the economy, has lurched from one crisis to another since 2021 after a regulatory crackdown on high leverage among developers triggered a liquidity crisis.
